    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fc2c8cee_88c4b411",
        "filename": "android/android-emugl/host/libs/Translator/EGL/EglOsApi_wgl.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 1022,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-20T18:22:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "well, but in that case we lock for quite a while - is it worth the efforts? knowing that we will eventually release some existing pbufs, so we may only need this one extra pbuf, not double the amount",
      "parentUuid": "8d94d29e_408e8502",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1016,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 1022,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "872eaa850d392a0c92d53277d1d9b3d3e46178e1",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "15b9a9a0_a3e9f5df",
        "filename": "android/android-emugl/host/libs/Translator/EGL/EglOsApi_wgl.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 1022,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-20T18:27:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, past a certain point it\u0027s difficult to create more pbufs. IMO though it\u0027s worth it since the more we pause to create pbufs the more lag there is; there\u0027s not a completely linear relationship between run time of pbuf creation and the # of pbufs created. Creating many pbufs in a batch seems to be much quicker than letting their creation spread over time too much.",
      "parentUuid": "fc2c8cee_88c4b411",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1016,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 1022,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "872eaa850d392a0c92d53277d1d9b3d3e46178e1",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
